%N A227210 Generalized Markoff numbers: largest of 7-tuple of positive numbers a, b, c, d, e, f, g satisfying the Markoff(7) equation a^2+b^2+c^2+d^2+e^2+f^2+g^2 = 2abcdefg.
%C A227210 No more terms below 2*10^5. Vieta jumping can be used to generate increasing roots. - _Tyler Yu_, Mar 12 2026
%e A227210 a(1)=2 and a(2)=6 since (2, 2, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1) and (6, 2, 2, 1, 1, 1, 1) satisfying a^2+b^2+c^2+d^2+e^2+f^2+g^2=2abcdefg with a>=b>=c>=d>=e>=f>=g. a(n) is the first components among all solutions in increasing order.
